Scheduler is DOWN. What happens?

A. Existing pods crash
B. New pods won’t be scheduled
C. Cluster stops working
D. etcd loses data

Solution:-
B. New pods won’t be scheduled.

Explanation:

• Existing pods → keep running
• New pods → stuck in Pending
• etcd → unaffected
• Cluster → partially functional

# Production Insight

 Deployments will appear “stuck”
 Autoscaling will fail
